Business Brief -- WIC Western International:
   Firm to Try Again to Gain
   Regulatory Approval of Sale
WIC, based in Vancouver, British Columbia, owns four TV
stations and a number of radio stations. Maclean Hunter is a
printing, publishing, cable TV and radio broadcasting
concern.
   Robert Furse, vice president, finance of Maclean Hunter,
said WIC is expected to provide the CRTC with testimony
regarding the impact of a forced sale of one of the British
Columbia stations. That issue didn't surface in the first
hearing.